10 "GOVOPS MODIFICATIONS
11 SECTION 6.7(a) G.S. 120-14 reads as rewritten:
12 "§ 120-14. Power of committees.
13 Any committee of investigation raised either by joint resolution or resolution of either house
14 of the General Assembly has full power to send for persons and papers, and, if necessary, to
15 compel attendance and production of papers by attachment or otherwise. Except as provided in
16 G.S. 105-259 or when expressly prohibited by federal law, production under this section shall
17 not be denied, delayed, redacted, or otherwise limited. Any confidential information obtained by
18 the Commission shall remain confidential and is not a public record as defined in G.S. 132-1."
19 SECTION 6.7(b) G.S. 120-19 reads as rewritten:
20 "§ 120-19. State officers, etc., upon request, to furnish data and information to legislative
21 committees or commissions.
22 Except as provided in G.S. 105-259, allAll officers, agents, agencies and departments of the
23 State are required toshall give to any committee of either house of the General Assembly, or any
24 committee or commission whose funds are appropriated or transferred to the General Assembly
25 or to the Legislative Services Commission for disbursement, upon request, all information and
26 all data within their possession, accessible or obtainable by them, or ascertainable from their
27 records. This requirement is mandatory and shall include requests made by any individual
28 member of the General Assembly, one of its standing committees or the chair of a standing
29 committee, or any other legislative panel duly appointed by the President Pro Tempore and/or
30 the Speaker of the House or an agent or employee of such a legislative panel.
31 This section supersedes and controls over any conflicting provision of State law other than
32 G.S. 105-259. No officer, agent, agency, or department of the State may deny, delay, redact, or
