7 SECTION 6.7(c) G.S. 120-77 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 120-77. Additional powers; confidentiality; penalties.
9 (a) The Commission shall have the power to compel the following in the discharge of its
10 duties under this Article:
11 (1) Access to any information, data, document or system of record held by a:
12 a. State agency pursuant to the provisions of G.S. 120-19.
13 b. Unit of local government or public authority.
14 c. A non-State entity receiving, directly or indirectly, public funds, to the
15 extent the documents information, data, document, or system of
16 record relate to the receipt, purpose, or implementation of a program
17 or service paid for with public funds.
18 (2) Attendance of any officer or employee officer, employee, agent, contractor,
19 subcontractor, consultant, vendor, grantee, subgrantee, attorney,
20 representative, or other person acting on behalf of any:
21 a. State agency.
22 b. Unit of local government or public authority.
23 c. Non-State entity receiving public funds provided the officer or
24 employee person associated with the entity that is required to attend is
25 responsible for for or has knowledge regarding implementing a
26 program or providing a service paid for with public funds.
27 (a1) This section supersedes and controls over any conflicting provision of State law other
28 than G.S. 105-259. A person or entity subject to this section may not deny, delay, redact, or
29 otherwise limit production of requested material except to the extent disclosure under this section
30 is expressly prohibited by federal law. Requested material accessible to a person or entity subject
31 to this section includes information and data accessible to an officer, employee, agent, contractor,
32 subcontractor, consultant, vendor, grantee, subgrantee, attorney, representative, or other person
33 acting on its behalf.
34 (b) Unless prohibited by federal law, the Commission and Commission staff shall be
35 provided access to all of the following in the discharge of their duties under this Article:
36 (1) Any building or facility allocated to or leased by a State agency.
37 (2) Any building or facility owned or leased by a unit of local government or
38 public authority.
39 (3) Any building or facility owned or leased by a non-State entity receiving public
40 funds provided (i) the building or facility is used to implement a program or
41 provide a service paid for with public funds and (ii) the access is reasonably
42 related to the receipt, purpose, or implementation of a program or service paid
43 for with public funds.

