1 (c) The Commission cochairs shall each designate one Commission staff member who
2 shall have access to the BEACON/HR payroll system.
3 (d) Any confidential information obtained by the Commission shall remain confidential
4 and is not a public record as defined in G.S. 132-1.
5 (e) Any document or information obtained or produced by Commission staff in
6 furtherance of staff's duties to the Commission is confidential and is not a public record as defined
7 in G.S. 132-1.
8 (f) Any request made to an agency employee by Commission staff and any
9 communication between Commission staff and an agency employee is confidential. An agency
10 employee shall treat as confidential to a member of Commission staff any request from and any
11 communication with the member. The nature and existence of the request and communications
12 shall only be revealed by an agency employee to another agency employee to the extent that it is
13 necessary to fulfill a request for document production or to gather more information as requested
14 by the member of Commission staff. A violation of this subsection by an agency employee shall
15 be grounds for disciplinary action, including dismissal.
16 (g) A person who conceals, destroys, alters, falsifies, or refuses to provide to the
17 Commission any document, information, data, testimony, system access, or access to any
18 building or facility as required by this Article with the intent to mislead, impede, or interfere with
19 the Commission's discharge of its duties under this Article shall be guilty of a Class 2
20 misdemeanor.
21 (h) The provisions of G.S. 120-19.1 through 120-19.4 shall apply to the proceedings of
22 the Commission as if it were a joint committee of the General Assembly."".
